# MyPetDex ‚Äî Cursor Rules
# Read this entire file before making any change to this project.

## What We're Building
MyPetDex is an iOS app that helps pet owners manage their pets' health, find local pet services, and connect with shelters. There is also a marketing website.

The project has TWO parts in this repo:
- `MyPetDex/` ‚Äî the Expo iOS app (branch: `main`)
- Root level ‚Äî the marketing website hosted on Vercel (branch: `master`)

---

## App: MyPetDex (Expo iOS)

### Core Rule: Expo Web SDK Only
- **NEVER** use React Native Firebase (`@react-native-firebase/*`)
- **NEVER** use native Firebase SDK
- **ALWAYS** use Firebase Web SDK (`firebase` npm package)
- **NEVER** suggest native modules unless they are already in `package.json`
- This is a pure **Expo** app ‚Äî all packages must be Expo-compatible

### Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Expo SDK 56, Expo Router (file-based routing)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Platform**: iOS only (no Android planned)
- **Auth**: `expo-auth-session` for Google OAuth, `expo-apple-authentication` for Apple Sign In
- **Database**: Firebase Firestore (Web SDK)
- **Storage**: Firebase Storage (Web SDK) ‚Äî photos uploaded via `XMLHttpRequest` blob method
- **Functions**: Firebase Cloud Functions v2 (`onCall`, `onRequest`)
- **Notifications**: `expo-notifications`
- **Error tracking**: Sentry (`@sentry/react-native`)
- **Image picker**: `expo-image-picker`
- **Browser**: `expo-web-browser` (SFSafariViewController ‚Äî stays in app)
- **Deep linking**: `expo-linking`

### Firebase Project
- Project ID: `mypetdex-c4315`
- Storage bucket: `mypetdex-c4315.firebasestorage.app`
- Auth domain: `auth.mypetdex.app`
- Bundle ID: `app.mypetdex`
- All Firebase config lives in `MyPetDex/lib/firebase.ts`

### Firestore Collections
- `users/{uid}` ‚Äî user profile (role, plan, email, displayName, pushToken, onboardingComplete)
- `users/{uid}/pets/{petId}` ‚Äî pet profiles (name, breed, age, weight, photoURL, status)
- `users/{uid}/pets/{petId}/records` ‚Äî vet/vaccine/medication records
- `users/{uid}/pets/{petId}/reminders` ‚Äî reminders
- `seedProviders` ‚Äî manually seeded service providers
- `shelter_pets` ‚Äî shelter/adoption listings
- `feedback` ‚Äî user feedback submissions
- `ingredients_master` ‚Äî food ingredients database
- `nutrient_targets` ‚Äî nutritional targets
- `recipes_vetted` ‚Äî vetted pet food recipes
- `shopProducts` ‚Äî pet shop product listings
- `reviews` ‚Äî provider reviews
- `siteReviews` ‚Äî website reviews
- `stats` ‚Äî app statistics

### User Roles
- `owner` ‚Äî pet owner (default)
- `provider` ‚Äî service provider (groomer, vet, trainer, walker, etc.)
- `shelter` ‚Äî animal shelter
- Admin: `mypetdexapp@gmail.com`

### Cloud Functions (deployed, live)
- `aiProxy` ‚Äî calls Anthropic Claude API for AI chat
- `getRecipe` ‚Äî generates pet food recipes via Claude
- `sendFeedback` ‚Äî sends feedback email via Resend
- `sendWelcomeEmail` ‚Äî sends welcome email on first verified login
- `notifyAdminFreeSignup` ‚Äî notifies admin of new signups
All functions use Firebase Secrets for sensitive keys ‚Äî never hardcode API keys in functions.

---

## API Keys ‚Äî Security Rules (CRITICAL)

### Where API keys live:
| Key | Where stored | How accessed |
|-----|-------------|--------------|
| Anthropic API key | Firebase Secret (`anthropic-key`) | `defineSecret()` in Cloud Functions only |
| Resend API key | Firebase Secret (`resend-key`) | `defineSecret()` in Cloud Functions only |
| Google OAuth Client IDs | `.env.local` (not committed) | `EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_IOS_CLIENT_ID`, `EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID` |
| RescueGroups API key | `.env.local` (not committed) | `EXPO_PUBLIC_RESCUEGROUPS_API_KEY` |
| Firebase config | `lib/firebase.ts` | Safe to be public ‚Äî restricted by bundle ID + domain in Firebase console |

### Rules:
- **NEVER** hardcode any API key in any file
- **NEVER** put secret keys in `app.json`, `eas.json`, or any committed file
- **NEVER** call Anthropic, Resend, or any paid external API directly from the app ‚Äî always go through a Cloud Function
- **NEVER** expose Firebase Secrets in client code
- If a new external API is needed, add it as a Firebase Secret and call it from a Cloud Function
- `.env.local` is gitignored ‚Äî always check before adding new env vars

---

## Build & Deploy Rules

### Development (free, no build needed):
```bash
npx expo start --dev-client --tunnel
```
Then open the MyPetDex dev app on iPhone and connect.

### Push code changes to dev (free OTA update):
```bash
eas update --channel development --message "description"
```

### Push fixes to production users (free OTA update ‚Äî no build):
```bash
eas update --channel production --message "description"
```
Use this for JS-only fixes. Production users get the update automatically.

### New App Store build (costs $2, only when necessary):
```bash
eas build --platform ios --profile production --auto-submit
```
Only needed for: new native packages, app.json changes (icons, permissions), or major version releases.

### NEVER suggest a production build for testing ‚Äî always use OTA update or dev client.

### Git branches:
- `main` ‚Äî Expo app code
- `master` ‚Äî marketing website only (Vercel watches `master`, not `main`)

