## Website: home.mypetdex.app
- Hosted on Vercel, connected to `master` branch
- Static HTML files: `privacy.html`, `terms.html`
- Domain: `home.mypetdex.app`
- App Store link: `https://apps.apple.com/app/mypetdex/id6772248051`
- **No API keys on the website** ‚Äî it is purely static HTML/CSS/JS
- Never add server-side code or environment variables to the website

---

## App Architecture

### Auth flow:
1. User opens app ‚Üí checks Firebase Auth state
2. Not logged in ‚Üí `/(auth)/sign-in.tsx`
3. Logged in but onboarding not complete ‚Üí `/(auth)/onboarding.tsx`
4. Fully set up ‚Üí `/(tabs)/` main app

### Navigation (Expo Router file-based):
- `/(tabs)/index.tsx` ‚Äî Home screen
- `/(tabs)/explore.tsx` ‚Äî Find services + adopt pets
- `/(tabs)/shopping.tsx` ‚Äî Pet shop
- `/(tabs)/ai.tsx` ‚Äî MyPetDex Assistant (AI chat)
- `/(tabs)/me.tsx` ‚Äî Profile, settings, feedback
- `/pet/[id].tsx` ‚Äî Pet detail page
- `/pet/add.tsx` ‚Äî Add new pet

### Key files:
- `MyPetDex/lib/firebase.ts` ‚Äî All Firebase initialization + helpers
- `MyPetDex/contexts/AuthContext.tsx` ‚Äî Auth state, Google/Apple sign-in logic
- `MyPetDex/app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx` ‚Äî Tab bar configuration
- `functions/index.js` ‚Äî All Cloud Functions

---

## Code Conventions
- Use `WebBrowser.openBrowserAsync()` for Privacy Policy, Terms ‚Äî never `Linking.openURL` for web pages
- Use `Linking.openURL` only for App Store links
- Always add `?tab=services` or `?tab=adopt` when navigating to `/(tabs)/explore` from anywhere in the app, so the correct tab is shown (never navigate to explore without a tab param)
- Phone numbers on provider cards must be tappable: wrap in a `Pressable` that calls `Linking.openURL(\`tel:${phone.replace(/\D/g, "")}\`)` and style the text in blue (`#4486F4`)
- All feedback goes through `callFunction("sendFeedback")` ‚Äî never `mailto:`
- Photo uploads use `XMLHttpRequest` blob method ‚Äî never `fetch().blob()` (broken in Expo's fetch)
- Never use `expo-file-system` for uploads
- Keyboard handling: wrap forms in `KeyboardAvoidingView behavior="padding"` on iOS
- Clear search state when user leaves a search screen (`useFocusEffect` or on unmount)
- Text strings must always be inside `<Text>` components ‚Äî never render raw strings in `<View>`
- Use `Boolean(value)` or `value != null` checks instead of `&&` with numbers/strings to avoid rendering `0` or `""` as text

